>why is there a rush to lower viscosity 
>base oil in the name of fuel economy?

- easier cold-weather starting
- more efficient lubrication
- reduced engine wear

>If it is
>the same viscosity at operating temp, how does it
>provide better fuel economy?  

The frictional properties of the oil vary from brand to brand within the same API viscosity classifications. Synthetics vary even more.

